menu "bb_cache_serialize"

config BB_CACHE_SERIALIZE_MAX_ENTRIES
    int "Maximum number of registered (format, key) render memo slots"
    default 8
    range 1 32
    help
        Fixed-size slot table capacity. Each slot holds one memoized
        rendered payload for a single (format, key) pair -- increase if
        more than 8 distinct wire endpoints are memoized via
        bb_cache_serialize_get() at once.

config BB_CACHE_SERIALIZE_BUF_BYTES
    int "Render memo slot buffer size (bytes)"
    default 512
    range 64 4096
    help
        Dual-budget knob -- this single value sizes BOTH the per-slot
        rendered wire bytes buffer (.bss, one per slot: standing cost is
        BB_CACHE_SERIALIZE_BUF_BYTES * BB_CACHE_SERIALIZE_MAX_ENTRIES bytes)
        AND the raw-struct snapshot scratch buffer (a stack array on the
        CALLING task, sized fresh for each bb_cache_serialize_get() call).
        Size it for the LARGER of the two requirements: the widest rendered
        JSON payload, or the largest owned struct being snapshotted. A
        render or snapshot whose size exceeds this fails with
        BB_ERR_NO_SPACE.

config BB_CACHE_SERIALIZE_MAX_KEYS
    int "Maximum number of registered (key -> descriptor) bindings"
    default 8
    range 1 32
    help
        Fixed-size descriptor registry capacity. Each entry binds one
        bb_cache key to its {descriptor, gather, ctx} via
        bb_cache_serialize_register() -- increase if more than 8 distinct
        keys register a serialize binding at once.

endmenu
